observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed that the:
Inventory Committee conduct a complete physical count of property and equipment and prepare and submit the RPCPPE to the Audit Team;
Municipal General Services Officer prepare the PCs for each PPE account and update the records regularly;
Municipal Accountant and General Services Officer both reconcile their records and do it regularly or every quarter, if possible; and
One-time cleansing of PPE account balances without available record of accountability should be availed of pursuant to the guidelines and procedures set forth in COA Circular No. 2020-006 to come up with reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to its existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended and the management agreed to:
a.	require the end user/in-charge of the program to sign the Job Order and Purchase Requests on future procurement of goods and services;
b.	attach the menu of snacks and meals catered on the disbursement vouchers as well as pictures during the catered dates;
c.	submit the list of vaccinees and workers who received the catered snacks, meals and bottled water as well as the Distribution list and proof of receipt for the recipient of the goods for distribution to the affected household;
d.	submit a copy of the ARE of the remaining one IT Equipment;
e.	submit the explanation on the necessity of the purchased bottled water, ice for air coolers and sakulin;
f.	pay directly to the supplier of goods and services as much as possible; and
g.	submit vaccination schedule for the year 2021.

We recommended that management require the Municipal Treasurer to:

Demand submission of Accountable Forms/Official Receipts still in the hands of three Collectors and account the collections and deposit immediately to the authorized government depository bank;
Require the Revenue Collectors to prepare the RAAF and then prepare CRAAF to consolidate the RAAFs.  Submit the required monthly reports in the prescribed forms provided in the NGAS Manual and submit the same not later than the fifth day of the ensuing month to the audit team;

We recommended to management the following:

Demand the immediate deposits to the authorized depository banks of the Municipality the government funds on the hands of the Former Acting Municipal Treasurer;
Demand the immediate remittance of the government funds on the hands of concerned AOs with a total amount of ₱3.052 million;
Require the Acting Municipal Treasurer to present immediately all unaccounted 259 pieces accountable forms, prepare RCD and remit the corresponding collections received thereof;
Require the Municipal Accountant to record in the books of account the unrecorded collections totaled to P3.967 million and the amount corresponding to 259 pieces accountable forms; and
Require Municipal Treasurer’s Office strictly comply of Section 69 of P.D. No. 1445.

We recommended that BAC Secretariat:

Submit copy of infrastructure contracts to COA within five working days from perfection thereof for review and evaluation pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001;
Document and monitor the flow or movement of the contracts to establish accountability for the non-submission of contracts for audit.

